- High earners are defined as individuals with an annual salary greater than $50,000; 
- Good health status refers to individuals who report their general health status as 'good'; 
- Disability status refers to individuals who report having a disability.

Small to medium-sized families refer to households with 2 to 4 family members; 
Employed individuals are those who have a steady income-generating job; 
Research data access frequency refers to the number of times an individual has accessed data for research purposes.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM individuals 
WHERE workclass_id IN (SELECT code_id FROM census_codes WHERE category = 'workclass');
